  "response": "The magic square problem has been studied by many mathematicians throughout history, but one of the most famous solutions was provided by the mathematician Leonhard Euler in the 18th century. Euler made significant contributions to the theory of magic squares, including the development of methods for constructing them and proving theorems about their properties. However, the study of magic squares dates back much further, to ancient China and other civilizations, and many other mathematicians have also made important contributions to the field.",
